sec.p:
Several different algorithms are available to perform batch correction [see, e.g., Fernández-Albert et al. (2014)]. Rather than do an exhaustive comparison of different approaches, we focus on the amount of information provided to the methods, and we consider two generic cases:
explicitly taking into account batch information and, possibly, injection sequence information. For this approach QCs can be used but are not required;
correction without explicit batch or injection sequence information. QCs are mandatory in this case.

