The second approach is based on the presence of biological replicates. The variation within one group (here: a genotype) consists of biological variation and technical variation. Batch correction should decrease the latter, so after correction the within-genotype variation is expected to be smaller than before correction. This can be measured by calculating, for each individual metabolite, the fraction of variance accounted for by the biological variation, also known as the repeatability: \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
